<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-07-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-07-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="670" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d670">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">McCormick</persName> to Acting Secretary of State <persName type="to">Adee</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-07-10"><hi rend="italic">July 10,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>France, with agreement of England, accepts invitation of Morocco to a
                            conference on the understanding with Germany that her rights are
                            respected, and that her arrangements with England and Spain will not be
                            questioned nor will the open-door policy be altered.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">McCormick.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>